               <p>
               <milestone n="1" unit="line"/>Hermias, son of Hermias, Πέρσης τῆς ἐπιγονῆς, to Leon, son of Orsenouphis, greetings. 
<milestone n="3" unit="line"/>I declare that I have received from you the three metretes of wine, including the half thereof, which I shall pay back to you in the month of Epeiph 
of the third year from my own vintage, new, good wine with the measure with which I usually pour out. <milestone n="11" unit="line"/>If, however, I do not pay it back as is written, 
I shall pay you three thousand copper drachmas for each keramion as fine. This document shall be valid wherever it may be produced. 
In the third year, the ninth Pachon. 
                <note>Translation: P.David 4</note>
              </p>
